## 🔬 Diagnosis Actor — How `POST /diagnoses` Works

### 1. The Request

```
POST http://localhost:9080/diagnoses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "diagnosisType": "io.leitstand.actor.events.diagnosis.NeRebootRequest",
  "diagnosisParameters": {
    "resourceId": "91000000-0080-0000-0103-000000000000"
  },
  "metadata": {
    "sourceObjectIdentifier": "91000000-0080-0000-0103-000000000000",
    "sourceObjectClass": "NetworkElement",
    "sourceObjectType": "A4-SPINE-Switch-v2"
  }
}
```

**Three parts in every request:**
- `diagnosisType` → Which operation to run (like a function name)
- `diagnosisParameters` → Arguments to that operation (like function arguments)
- `metadata` → Who/what this operation is about (the network element)

---

### 2. Step-by-Step Flow

```
Browser/curl
    │
    │  POST /diagnoses (JSON body)
    ▼
[cmd/actors/diagnosis/main.go]
    │  startService() mounts the router at "/"
    │  → mux.Handle("/", diagnosisRouter)
    ▼
[pkg/resources/diagnoses.go]  runDiagnosis()
    │
    ├─ Step 1: Deserialize JSON body into a "request" struct
    │           diagnosisType      = "...NeRebootRequest"
    │           diagnosisParameters = {"resourceId": "..."}
    │           metadata            = {sourceObjectIdentifier, ...}
    │
    ├─ Step 2: Look up the "diagnosisType" in the schema registry
    │           → finds the Go struct that matches this type name
    │           → gets a deserializer function for it
    │
    ├─ Step 3: Deserialize diagnosisParameters into typed Go struct
    │           {"resourceId": "..."} → NeRebootRequest{ResourceId: "..."}
    │
    ├─ Step 4: Set up two callbacks (functions to call later)
    │           sendDiagnosis() → writes success response to HTTP client
    │           sendError()     → writes error/timeout response to HTTP client
    │
    ├─ Step 5: Call newEmit() to publish to NATS message bus
    │           Subject: "diagnosis-validated-requests"
    │           Wraps the payload in a DiagnosisRequest envelope (Avro binary)
    │           Sets metadata fields on the event
    │
    ├─ Step 6: Wait (up to 60 seconds) for a response
    │           select {
    │             case <-done:           → callback was called, response sent
    │             case <-time.After(60s):→ timeout, connection closes
    │           }
    │
    │  [Meanwhile, on the NATS message bus...]
    ▼
[pkg/fixtures/diagnosis/diagnosis.go]  Pipeline
    │  Listening on "diagnosis-validated-requests"
    │  Matches message type → routes to commands.RebootDevice()
    ▼
[pkg/fixtures/diagnosis/ne_reboot_command.go]  RebootDevice()
    │
    ├─ Validate sourceObjectClass == "NetworkElement"
    ├─ Validate sourceObjectType is a supported switch type
    ├─ Fetch network element from inventory
    ├─ Get management IP address
    └─ Call switchClient.Reboot()  ← actual Juniper API call
         │
         └─ Returns NeRebootResponse{ReturnCode: {Code: "OK", ...}}
    │
    ▼
Pipeline publishes NeRebootResponse to NATS "diagnosis-responses"
    │
    ▼
newEmit() response listener receives it
    │  Unwraps envelope → calls sendDiagnosis() callback
    ▼
sendDiagnosis() writes HTTP response back to caller
    │
    └─ 200 OK: {"id": "...", "responseData": {"rebootResult": {...}}}
```

---

### 3. Key Code in `diagnoses.go`

```go
