## ⚙️ Command Actor — How `POST /commands` Works

### 1. The Request

```
POST http://localhost:9081/commands
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "commandType": "io.leitstand.actor.events.commands.NeRebootCommandRequest",
  "commandParameters": {
    "resourceId": "91000000-0080-0000-0103-000000000000",
    "rebootMode": "DEFAULT"
  },
  "metadata": {
    "sourceObjectIdentifier": "91000000-0080-0000-0103-000000000000",
    "sourceObjectClass": "NetworkElement",
    "sourceObjectType": "A4-SPINE-Switch-v2"
  }
}
```

Same three-part structure, just with `commandType` and `commandParameters` instead of the `diagnosis*` equivalents.

---

### 2. Step-by-Step Flow

```
Browser/curl
    │
    │  POST /commands (JSON body)
    ▼
[cmd/actors/command/main.go]
    │  startService() mounts the router at "/"
    │  → mux.Handle("/", commandRouter)
    ▼
[pkg/resources/commands.go]  runCommand()
    │
    ├─ Step 1-5: Same as diagnosis actor
    │             (deserialize → registry lookup → typed struct → callbacks → publish)
    │             BUT publishes to "command-validated-requests" subject
    │             AND wraps in CommandRequest envelope (not DiagnosisRequest)
    │
    ├─ Step 6: Wait (up to 40 MINUTES) for a response  ← big difference!
    │
    │  [Meanwhile, on the NATS message bus...]
    ▼
[pkg/fixtures/commands/commands.go]  Pipeline
    │  Listening on NATS DefaultSubject
    │  Matches message type → routes to commands.NeReboot()
    ▼
[pkg/fixtures/commands/ne_reboot.go]  NeReboot()  →  rebootDeviceSync()
    │
    ├─ Validate sourceObjectClass == "NetworkElement"
    ├─ Validate sourceObjectType is a supported switch type
    ├─ Fetch network element from inventory
    ├─ Get management IP + full metadata (MatNumber, Hostname, NeConfigID...)
    ├─ Call switchClient.Reboot()  ← actual Juniper API call
    │
    │  *** EXTRA: Post-reboot monitoring loop ***
    │
    ├─ PerformPing() — Shutdown verification loop
    │     Pings every 10s for up to 2 minutes
    │     Waits until device STOPS responding (confirms it shut down)
    │     Produces CommandProcessingProgress events to Kafka
    │
    ├─ PerformPing() — Bootup verification loop
    │     Pings every 30s for up to 30 minutes
    │     Waits until device STARTS responding again (confirms it rebooted)
    │     Produces CommandProcessingProgress events to Kafka
    │
    └─ ProduceNeRebootCommandResponse()
         Produces final CommandResponse to Kafka
    │
    ▼
Pipeline publishes CommandResponse to "command-responses"
    │
    ▼
newCommandEmit() response listener receives it
    │  Unwraps envelope → calls sendCommand() callback
    ▼
sendCommand() writes HTTP response back to caller
    │
    └─ 200 OK: {"id": "...", "responseData": {"summary": "...", "details": "..."}}
```

---

