## ⚖️ Differences: Diagnosis vs Command

| Aspect | Diagnosis Actor | Command Actor |
|---|---|---|
| **Purpose** | Diagnostics + fire-and-return operations (includes reboot trigger) | Device operations with active post-operation monitoring |
| **Endpoint** | `POST /diagnoses` | `POST /commands` |
| **Request field** | `diagnosisType` / `diagnosisParameters` | `commandType` / `commandParameters` |
| **NATS subject (request)** | `diagnosis-validated-requests` | `command-validated-requests` |
| **NATS subject (response)** | `diagnosis-responses` | `command-responses` |
| **Message envelope** | `DiagnosisRequest` / `DiagnosisResponse` | `CommandRequest` / `CommandResponse` |
| **Output sink** | NATS | **Kafka** |
| **HTTP timeout** | 60 seconds | **40 minutes** |
| **Post-operation monitoring** | ❌ None — fire and return | ✅ Ping loops (shutdown + bootup) |
| **Progress events** | ❌ None | ✅ `CommandProcessingProgress`, `CommandProcessingFailed`, `CommandProcessingFinished` |
| **Response has return code** | ✅ `returnCode.code` (`OK`, `BAD_REQUEST`, etc.) | ❌ Just `summary` + `details` |
| **Metadata richness** | Minimal (`NeId`, `IP`) | Full (`MatNumber`, `Hostname`, `NeType`, `NeConfigID`, ...) |

